  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Line a large baking tin with cling film, making sure there's some overhang."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pour the cream into a large bowl and whisk into soft peaks. Pour in the condensed milk, vanilla extract and sea salt. Fold it to combine, then pour into your lined baking tin. Transfer to the freezer and set for at least 2 hours, or overnight."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cut off the end of a piping bag, and use a star nozzle if you have one, it's not essential but I like it. Using the cling film to help you, remove the ice cream from the baking tin and cut into pieces. Quickly transfer to a large mixing bowl and whip up using an electric whisk, or if you have it – a stand mixer. Scoop it into your piping bag and swirl into cones. Top with your choice of toppings and get stuck in!"
    }
